gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bucks 119, Cavaliers 111
gameRecap.excerpt: The Bucks defeated the Cavaliers, 119-111. Giannis Antetokounmpo recorded 34 points, 16 rebounds, and five assists for the Bucks, while Damian Lillard added 31 points and four assists in the victory. Donovan Mitchell (34 points, nine assists) and Jarrett Allen (career-high 30 points, 12 rebounds, six assists) combined for 64 points for the Cavaliers in the losing effort. The Bucks have won back-to-back games as they improve to 24-8, while the Cavaliers fall to 18-14.
